
Overview of noun compensation

The noun compensation has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                   
1. (6) compensation -- (something (such as money) given or received as payment or reparation (as for a service or loss or injury))
2. compensation -- ((psychiatry) a defense mechanism that conceals your undesirable shortcomings by exaggerating desirable behaviors)
3. recompense, compensation -- (the act of compensating for service or loss or injury)
